The paper discusses choreography-based programming, which is a programming paradigm for defining communication-based systems from a global viewpoint. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the reduction of the number of communications and resources needed to execute a choreography, which suggests that it may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the composition of existing protocols to obtain new ones, which suggests that it may belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of behavioural types, which are a type of formal specification, suggesting that it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses a transformation from a choreography with a possibly unbounded number of protocol instantiations to a choreography instantiating a single protocol, which suggests that it may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category.
